7 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
8 An Act relating to property; providing setback
requirements for solar energy and industrial battery
9 storage facilities; providing for codification; and
declaring an emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1501 of Title 60, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 Solar energy and industrial battery storage facilities,
17 excluding residential solar energy panels, shall have the following
18 setback requirements:
19 1. Shall not be located within three hundred (300) feet of an
20 occupied structure or occupied residence unless waived in writing by
21 the owner of the structure or residence;
22 2. Shall not be located within one hundred (100) feet of any
23 outer boundary of the facility property; and
24
